            HackerEarth's strength is its developer community and sourcing capabilities — hackathons and hiring challenges can attract candidates beyond your existing pipeline. AssessIQ is a private B2B assessment platform with no public community or leaderboards, focused on structured, rubric-based assessments with audit trails. AssessIQ suits teams that want a controlled, branded process; HackerEarth suits teams that want to source candidates via community engagement.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-b border-aiq-border pb-aiq-xl">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-aiq-xl font-normal tracking-aiq-tight text-aiq-fg-primary mb-aiq-sm mt-0">Does HackerEarth have a free tier?</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-aiq-md text-aiq-fg-secondary leading-relaxed m-0">
            HackerEarth has offered free starter access historically. Pricing varies by plan and usage; check hackerearth.com/recruit for current terms. AssessIQ also offers a free tier — see <a href="/pricing" class="text-aiq-accent hover:text-aiq-accent-hover underline underline-offset-2">/pricing</a> for details.
